FAKE NEWS DETECTION USING MACHINE LEARNING
1. Introduction

Fake News Detection is a Machine Learning application that identifies whether a news article is real or fake based on its textual content. Due to the rapid growth of social media and online news platforms, fake news spreads quickly and can mislead people. This project uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning techniques to classify news articles as Real News or Fake News.

2. Objective

The main objective of this project is:

  *To detect fake news automatically.
  *To preprocess textual news data.
  *To convert text into numerical features using TF-IDF.
  *To train a Machine Learning model for classification.
  *To predict whether a user-entered news article is real or fake.
