4. Modules
  4.1 Data Collection Module
    News data is collected from an Excel dataset.
      Dataset contains:
        Title
        News Text
        Label (Real/Fake)

  4.2 Data Preprocessing Module

    This module cleans the text data by:

      Removing special characters
      Converting text to lowercase
      Removing stop words
      Applying stemming using Porter Stemmer

4.3 Feature Extraction Module
  TF-IDF Vectorizer is used.
  Converts text into numerical vectors.
  Important words receive higher weights.

4.4 Model Training Module
  Logistic Regression algorithm is used.
  Dataset is divided into:
  Training Data (80%)
  Testing Data (20%)

4.5 Prediction Module
  User enters a news statement.
  Text is preprocessed.
  TF-IDF transformation is applied.
  Model predicts:
  Real News
  Fake News

4.6 Evaluation Module
  Accuracy Score is calculated.
  Model performance is evaluated using test data.

5. Algorithm Used
  Logistic Regression

Logistic Regression is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for binary classification problems.

Advantages:

Simple and efficient.
Fast training process.
Suitable for text classification.
Good performance on large datasets.

6. Working Procedure

Step 1: Load Dataset
Read news dataset from Excel file.

Step 2: Handle Missing Values
Empty values are replaced with blank strings.

Step 3: Text Preprocessing
Remove unwanted characters.
Convert to lowercase.
Remove stop words.
Apply stemming.

Step 4: Feature Extraction
Convert text into TF-IDF vectors.

Step 5: Train-Test Split
Split dataset into training and testing sets.

Step 6: Model Training
Train Logistic Regression model.

Step 7: Prediction
Predict fake or real news.

Step 8: Accuracy Calculation
Calculate model accuracy.

